rComments: This teacher seem to know are subject however she has difficulty to teach. The lessons are confusing and not enough examples are done in class. She seems like a nice person, but her lectures didn't make much sense and focused way too much on theory with very few worked examples. Her tests, assignments, formula sheets, and notes all had mistakes in them, which was pretty annoying. Overall it was an easy course, but I ended up teaching myself most of it. Tests were of reasonable difficulty.

She will teach primarily from conceptual perspective, not rote learning of formulas. So her teaching could benefit from more examples, but show up to class and she gives clear signals on how to interpret exam questions and what will be on midterm/final. Her notes summarize the material very well. The assignments/tests are very fair.
she teaches a confusing lecture without giving clear examples of each type of questions, fair midterm though.
